<p>
La Caribeana Futurismo which is an aesthetic, ideology, and identity. The power of visualizing the divine feminine within the future with unlimited power requires a certain je ne se quoi that stems from the foundation of black girl magic.  
 
Context hailing from the island of St. Croix a mixture of borkien/taino history and heritage mixed with the west African ideologies/spirtualities of Benin, and a dash of Irish folklore/dance/tradition comes a concept called la caribeana futurismo which in english means The Caribbean Woman’s futurism. An inspiration from afrofuturism that has shaped the concept from its core. Black culture is everywhere so there needs to be an understanding that within the many facets of this identity their lives a side with distinctive themes. 
</p>

